model_solution:
## Step 1: We need to compute $\dbinom{10}{4}$.
$\dbinom{10}{4}$ = $\dfrac{10!}{4!(10-4)!}$
## Step 2: Compute the factorials.
$\dfrac{10!}{4!(10-4)!}$ = $\dfrac{10!}{4!6!}$ = $\dfrac{10 \cdot 9 \cdot 8 \cdot 7 \cdot 6!}{4 \cdot 3 \cdot 2 \cdot 1 \cdot 6!}$

Final Answer: $\boxed{210}$
